The paper deals with algorithms for computing convex hulls, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves randomized algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of randomness and probability also suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GR (Graphics).
